com.metrics.common.sets

Class MetricsSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractList<E>
        • java.util.ArrayList<Item>
          • com.metrics.common.sets.MetricsSet
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<Item>, Collection<Item>, List<Item>, RandomAccess

    public class MetricsSet
extends ArrayList<Item>
    Map of a set of metrics; key is the unique identifier for the set of metrics (e.g., a CUSIP or a trade identifier); the values are maps of key-value pairs containing detailed metrics.

    NOTE: the identifier is included in the map of metrics, allowing the map of metrics to precisely reflect the entire contents of an underlying data file.

      • inferTypes

        public void inferTypes()
        Attempt to detect and re-cast data fields that contain doubles, integers or dates. Will proceed to re-cast a field only if 100% of items containing that field can be successfully re-cast; if any item fails for a given field, that field is not re-cast.

      • inferTypes

        public void inferTypes(boolean parseDatesIntoDateObjects,
              String... skipTheseTags)
        Attempt to detect and re-cast data fields that contain doubles, integers or dates. Will proceed to re-cast a field only if 100% of items containing that field can be successfully re-cast; if any item fails for a given field, that field is not re-cast. Skips specified tags.

      • recastValues

        public void recastValues()
                  throws ValidationException
        Attempt to recast type of every string value, individually, in the following order: 1. Integer 2. Double 3. Date (as an int, for example 20140115)

        ValidationException
